# Preppod Backend Development Guide

## Project Structure and Architecture

### Domain-Driven Design (DDD) Implementation
- Follow Domain-Driven Design principles
- Organize code into bounded contexts and subdomains
- Use ubiquitous language throughout the codebase
- Implement rich domain models with business logic

### Subdomain Structure
```
src/subdomains/
├── {subdomain-name}/
│   ├── api/                    # API layer (controllers, DTOs, middleware)
│   ├── application/            # Application layer (services, factories)
│   ├── infrastructure/         # Infrastructure layer (repositories, external services)
│   ├── domains/                # Domain layer (entities, value objects, enums)
│   └── {subdomain-name}.module.ts
```

### Creating a New Subdomain
1. Create the subdomain directory structure
2. Implement layers in order:
   - Domain (entities, enums, interfaces)
   - Infrastructure (repositories, external services)
   - Application (services, factories)
   - API (controllers, DTOs)
3. Create the subdomain module
4. Register in the root module

### Layer Responsibilities

#### Domain Layer
- Define core business entities and value objects
- Implement domain logic and business rules
- Define interfaces for repositories
- Create enums and constants
- No external dependencies

#### Infrastructure Layer
- Implement repository interfaces
- Handle database operations
- Manage external service integrations
- Implement caching mechanisms
- Handle file storage and retrieval

#### Application Layer
- Implement use cases and business logic
- Coordinate between domain and infrastructure
- Handle transactions and unit of work
- Implement factories for domain objects
- Manage application services

#### API Layer
- Define REST controllers
- Handle request/response mapping
- Implement middleware
- Define DTOs for input/output
- Handle authentication and authorization

