## Testing Guidelines

### Test Structure
```
src/subdomains/{subdomain-name}/
├── api/
│   ├── rest/
│   │   ├── dto/
│   │   │   ├── input/
│   │   │   │   └── __mocks__/        # Mock DTOs for input
│   │   │   └── output/
│   │   │       └── __mocks__/        # Mock DTOs for output
│   │   └── controllers/
│   │       └── __tests__/            # Controller tests
├── application/
│   ├── factories/
│   │   └── __tests__/                # Factory tests
│   ├── services/
│   │   └── __tests__/                # Service tests
│   └── __tests__/                    # Application layer tests
├── domains/
│   ├── entities/
│   │   └── __mocks__/                # Entity mocks
│   ├── enums/
│   │   └── __tests__/                # Enum tests
│   └── __tests__/                    # Domain layer tests
└── infrastructure/
    ├── repositories/
    │   └── __tests__/                # Repository tests
    └── __tests__/                    # Infrastructure layer tests
```

### Test File Naming Convention
- Test files should be named with `.test.ts` or `.spec.ts` suffix
- Mock files should be placed in `__mocks__` directories
- Test files should mirror the structure of the source files

### Mock Structure
- Create mock classes for entities and DTOs
- Use static factory methods for creating mock instances
- Include default values and allow overrides
- Group related mocks in `__mocks__` directories

Example mock structure:
```typescript
// src/subdomains/{subdomain}/domains/entities/__mocks__/entity.mock.ts
export class EntityMock {
  static create(overrides: Partial<Entity> = {}): Entity {
    const entity = new Entity();
    // Set default values
    Object.assign(entity, overrides);
    return entity;
  }
}

// src/subdomains/{subdomain}/api/rest/dto/input/__mocks__/dto.mock.ts
export class DtoMock {
  static create(overrides: Partial<Dto> = {}): Dto {
    const dto = new Dto();
    // Set default values
    Object.assign(dto, overrides);
    return dto;
  }
}
```

### Test Categories

1. Unit Tests
   - Test individual components in isolation
   - Use mocks for dependencies
   - Focus on business logic
   - Use Jest/Testing Library
   - Follow the pattern:
     ```typescript
     describe('Component', () => {
       describe('method', () => {
         it('should do something', () => {
           // Test implementation
         });
       });
     });
     ```

2. Integration Tests
   - Test component interactions
   - Use test database
   - Test repository operations
   - Verify service integration
   - Include transaction management tests

3. E2E Tests
   - Test complete workflows
   - Use test environment
   - Verify API endpoints
   - Test authentication flow
   - Include error scenarios

### Test Coverage
- Aim for high coverage of business logic
- Focus on critical paths
- Include edge cases
- Test error scenarios
- Document test cases

## Database Migrations

### Migration Structure
```
src/aop/db/migrations/
├── {timestamp}_{migration-name}.ts
```

### Creating Migrations
1. Use TypeORM migration commands
2. Follow naming convention: `{timestamp}_{description}`
3. Include up and down methods
4. Document schema changes
5. Ensure the timestamp is the latest

### Migration Best Practices
- Keep migrations atomic
- Include rollback methods
- Test migrations in development
- Document schema changes
- Use transactions for data migrations

